title: a1278_a3115b does not turn on
message:
I have a situation similar to the example of the rossman wiki.

Green light, does not turn on - 0.03A power source
------------------------------------------
PP5V_S3 = 0V
P5VS3_EN_L was 1.42V to ENTRIP1 on TPS51125 (U7200)
When Q7221 was removed, PP5V_S3 was good (5V)
PM_SLP_S4_L = 0V on pin 1 of Q7911

PM_SLP_S4_L should be high, right?

Bad PCH or any recommendation?

title: a1278_a3115b does not turn on
message:
=PP5VS3_EN_L  should be 0V, to enable 5V_S3.
1.42V is very strange.
Do you get correct 3V42_G3H voltage?
